---
// Open-core topology, rendered with semantic HTML + CSS (no images, no JS).
// Left: free LAN-only player. Right: optional self-hosted managed relay the
// operator runs. The Pi dials OUT over WireGuard — nothing inbound is exposed.
---
<figure class="diagram" aria-label="Architecture: Raspberry Pi players behind NAT dial out over WireGuard to a self-hosted relay that the operator runs; the operator manages the fleet from a console.">
  <div class="d-grid">
    <div class="d-col">
      <span class="d-tag pill pill-live">Community · LAN</span>
      <div class="d-node player">
        <strong>Raspberry Pi player</strong>
        <small>Chromium kiosk · plays offline · admin on the LAN</small>
      </div>
      <p class="d-caption">Free &amp; open source. Runs standalone — no internet required to keep playing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="d-link" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="d-nat">NAT / firewall</span>
      <span class="d-arrow">WireGuard ⟶ outbound only</span>
    </div>

    <div class="d-col">
      <span class="d-tag pill pill-live">Pro · Managed relay</span>
      <div class="d-node relay">
        <strong>Self-hosted relay</strong>
        <small>You run it. EU / your server. Enrollment · heartbeat · commands</small>
      </div>
      <div class="d-node console">
        <strong>Fleet console</strong>
        <small>See every screen · reboot · screenshot · push content</small>
      </div>
      <p class="d-caption">Optional. The operator owns the relay and the data — not a third-party cloud.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <figcaption class="visually-hidden">
    Players behind NAT enroll outbound over WireGuard to a relay the operator self-hosts; the operator manages the fleet from a console. No inbound ports are opened on the players.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .diagram { margin: 0; }
  .d-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr; gap: 1rem; align-items: stretch; }
  .d-col { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.7rem; }
  .d-tag { align-self: flex-start; }
  .d-node { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.1rem; }
  .d-node strong { display: block; color: var(--text); font-size: 1rem; }
  .d-node small { color: var(--text-mut); font-size: 0.84rem; }
  .d-node.relay { border-color: var(--amber-line); background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-card), rgba(245,166,35,0.05)); }
  .d-node.console { border-style: dashed; }
  .d-caption { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-mut); margin: 0.2rem 0 0; }
  .d-link { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 0 0.5rem; min-width: 130px; text-align: center; }
  .d-nat { font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--text-mut); border: 1px dashed var(--border-strong); border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.3rem 0.5rem; }
  .d-arrow { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--amber-bright); font-weight: 600; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .d-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .d-link { flex-direction: row; min-width: 0; padding: 0.4rem 0; gap: 0.8rem; }
    .d-arrow::before { content: '↓ '; }
  }
</style>
